15 \n1716         The default, ``None``, means `sys.stdout`.\n1717 \n1718     *args, **kwargs\n1719         The properties to set.  The following combinations are supported:\n1720 \n1721         - Set the linestyle of a line to be dashed:\n1722 \n1723           >>> line, = plot([1, 2, 3])\n1724           >>> setp(line, linestyle=\'--\')\n1725 \n1726         - Set multiple properties at once:\n1727 \n1728           >>> setp(line, linewidth=2, color=\'r\')\n1729 \n1730         - List allowed values for a line\'s linestyle:\n1731 \n1732           >>> setp(line, \'linestyle\')\n1733           linestyle: {\'-\', \'--\', \'-.\', \':\', \'\', (offset, on-off-seq), ...}\n1734 \n1735         - List all properties that can be set, and their allowed values:\n1736 \n1737           >>> setp(line)\n1738           agg_filter: a filter function, ...\n1739           [long output listing omitted]\n1740 \n1741         `setp` also supports MATLAB style string/value pairs.  For example, the\n1742         following are equivalent:\n1743 \n1744         >>> setp(lines, \'linewidth\', 2, \'color\', \'r\')  # MATLAB style\n1745         >>> setp(lines, linewidth=2, color=\'r\')        # Python style\n1746 \n1747     See Also\n1748     --------\n1749     getp\n1750     """\n1751 \n1752     if isinstance(obj, Artist):\n1753         objs = [obj]\n1754     else:\n1755         objs = list(cbook.flatten(obj))\n1756 \n1757     if not objs:\n1758         return\n1759 \n1760     insp = ArtistInspector(objs[0])\n1761 \n1762     if not kwargs and len(args) < 2:\n1763         if args:\n1764             print(insp.pprint_setters(prop=args[0]), file=file)\n1765         else:\n1766             print(\'\\n\'.join(insp.pprint_setters()), file=file)\n1767         return\n1768 \n1769     if len(args) % 2:\n1770         raise ValueError(\'The set args must be string, value pairs\')\n1771 \n1772     funcvals = dict(zip(args[::2], args[1::2]))\n1773     ret = [o.update(funcvals) for o in objs] + [o.set(**kwargs) f